"title": "4010: creation, renewal of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4010",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's creation, spoilt by sin, will one day be completely renewed. The old order will pass away and a new everlasting order established.</p>\n<h2>The renewal of creation</h2>\n<h3>The passing away of the old order</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10-2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:10–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:25-Ps102:26\">PSA 102:25–102:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:4\">ISA 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:6\">ISA 51:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:18\">MAT 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:35\">MAT 24:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:14\">REV 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></p>\n<h3>The expectancy of nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:22\">ROM 8:19–8:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:29\">GEN 5:29</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's destruction of all his enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:24–15:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:34-Acts2:35\">ACT 2:34–2:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:13\">HEB 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:13\">HEB 10:13</a></p>\n<h3>The new heavens and new earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1-Rev21:2\">REV 21:1–21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17\">ISA 65:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:22\">ISA 66:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:21\">ACT 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:10\">HEB 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:16\">HEB 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22\">HEB 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:3-Rev21:5\">REV 21:3–21:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:10\">REV 21:10</a></p>\n<h3>The purity of the new creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:27\">REV 21:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:20\">PSA 37:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:1\">ISA 52:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:17\">JOL 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:14-Rev22:15\">REV 22:14–22:15</a></p>\n<h2>The creation of the new humanity</h2>\n<h3>The new birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:3\">JHN 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5-John3:8\">JHN 3:5–3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4\">ROM 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:15\">GAL 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:15\">EPH 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Renewal in God's image</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:10\">COL 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:24\">EPH 4:24</a></p>\n<h3>A new heart and a new spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26\">EZK 36:26</a></strong> <em>“new” refers to the work of the Holy Spirit in renewing Christians as they believe in Jesus Christ. This renewing will be complete in the new creation.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:19\">EZK 11:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:31\">EZK 18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:16\">2CO 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>A new mind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:23\">EPH 4:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a></p>\n<h3>A new song</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:3\">PSA 33:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:3\">PSA 40:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:9\">PSA 144:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:1\">PSA 149:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:10\">ISA 42:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:3\">REV 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3-Rev15:4\">REV 15:3–15:4</a></p>\n<h2>The future glorification of humanity</h2>\n<h3>The desire for a new body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23-Rom8:25\">ROM 8:23–8:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17-Rom8:18\">ROM 8:17–8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:1-2Cor5:5\">2CO 5:1–5:5</a></p>\n<h3>The resurrection of a new body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:11\">ROM 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25-Job19:27\">JOB 19:25–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2-Dan12:3\">DAN 12:2–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:28-John5:29\">JHN 5:28–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:15\">ACT 24:15</a></p>\n<h3>The nature of the resurrection body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:42-1Cor15:54\">1CO 15:42–15:54</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of sorrow and pain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:7-Isa25:8\">ISA 25:7–25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:20\">ISA 60:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:19\">ISA 65:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:17\">REV 7:17</a></p>\n<h3>A new name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:5\">ISA 56:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:2\">ISA 62:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:15\">ISA 65:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:17\">REV 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>A new home</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:2\">JHN 14:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:1\">2CO 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>God will dwell with his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:3\">REV 21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek48:35\">EZK 48:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:10\">ZEC 2:10</a></p>",
